ological questions about the functions and the institutional history of fictionality since ancient times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFictionxHistory and criticism. 0aFictions, Theory of. 0aLiteraturexPhilosophy. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 4aFiktion. 4aFiktionalität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aFiction.1 aBareis, J. Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristmann, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlauch, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroeben, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaas, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlauk, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlauk, Tobias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKonrad, Eva-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöppe, Tilmann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöppe, Tilmann, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOnea, Edgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReicher, Maria Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRösler, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScholz, Oliver R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThon, Jan-Noël, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVendrell Ferran, Íngrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWenninger, Regina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWerner, Jan C., econtributor.4ctb